text.section:
The petition for the voluntary termination of parental rights shall be filed in the Circuit Court of the judicial circuit where the petitioner or child resides or in the Circuit Court in the county in which juvenile court actions, if any, concerning the child have commenced, and shall be verified and contain the following:
Name and place of residence of each petitioner;
Name, sex, date of birth, and place of residence of the child;
Name and relationship of each petitioner to the child;
A concise statement of the factual basis for the termination of parental rights;
Name and address of the person or of the cabinet or authorized agency to which parental rights are sought to be transferred; and
A statement that the person, cabinet, or authorized agency to whom custody is to be given has facilities available, is willing to receive the custody of the child, and the person, if not excepted by KRS 199.470(4) or (5), has applied for the written permission of the secretary or the secretary's designee for the child's placement. This provision shall not affect the right of a court to grant temporary custody under KRS 199.473.
